## 2.3.2.3 Verification Of Step Detector Operation With Exclusion Capability

Simulate a satellite scenario as follows:

1) Correct Exclusion: The right satellite is excluded before the position error 
exceeds the HAL (HPLFD in this test) for longer than the time to alert; 
2) Failed Exclusion: A navigation alert is output due to detected positioning failure; 
or 
3) Missed Alert: The position error exceeds the HAL (HPLFD in this test) for longer 
than the time-to-alert without a navigation alert (this could be due to missed detection or wrong exclusion).
